article.headline: Marist 83, Liberty 69
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Jared Jordan and Will Whittington each had 18 points and all five starters scored in double digits as Marist beat Liberty 83-69 Tuesday night. Ryan Stliphen had 14 for Marist (6-6), Carl Hood had 12 and James Smith had 10. Smith and Hood each had 11 rebounds as Marist outrebounded the Flames 45-31. Marist had 15 second-chance points to just five for Liberty (4-10). The Red Foxes turned 14 Liberty turnovers into 27 points, 17 in the first half. Marist jumped out to an 11-0 lead in the first four minutes and led 37-28 at halftime. Marist went on a 9-1 run to open the second half, but Liberty tied it off two free throws by Damian Hubbard. Liberty went ahead by as many as five, but couldn't hold on. Marist regained the lead off Jordan's layup with 11:26 remaining. The Flames stayed within five until the final 3½ minutes, when Jordan had six points and Hood scored five. Larry Blair led Liberty with 18 points, and Anthony Smith and Hubbard each had 10. Three Liberty players fouled out, as did two from Marist.
